1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,639
Am I forgiven?

3
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:02,160
Of course.

4
00:00:02,320 --> 00:00:04,560
I'm glad to have you in my life.

5
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:05,919
I'm annoying like that.

6
00:00:05,920 --> 00:00:07,080
If you can handle that, stay.

7
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:07,840
If not, walk away.

8
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:10,240
Someone like you is exactly my type.

9
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,439
Romeo, I want to stay with you tonight.

10
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:13,440
Can I?

11
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,320
Dean and I are getting back together.

12
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:21,320
Guess I have to admit it.

13
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:22,521
I do want to take care of him.

14
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,800
(Episode 8: Intermission)

15
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,960
I haven't been on a
date with you in forever...

16
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,520
I remember when I first moved to Bangkok,

17
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:30,079
you were the one showing me around.

18
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:30,880
Remember?

19
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:34,080
Then you got lost in all the lights
and never found your way back.

20
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,560
That's on you.

21
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:38,160
You never take the blame, do you?

22
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,280
Hm?

23
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:40,800
Excuse me.

24
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,640
No public displays of
affection in this gallery.

25
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:47,880
- Hey!
- Hey!
Top. Mew.

26
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,936
What are you guys doing here?

27
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,760
I'm shooting promo photos.

28
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:54,240
My senior owns this gallery.
They asked me to help out.

29
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:55,800
Ah.

30
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:58,160
You two are a power couple now.
Very famous.

31
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,000
We're not. You're exaggerating.

32
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,879
Oh, you are. I'm following you.

33
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:05,560
I saw your cat café review. It was so cute.

34
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,760
Top likes cats. That's why we went.

35
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,639
That's why I got myself a boyfriend
that looks like one.

36
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:11,480
Look at him.

37
00:02:11,481 --> 00:02:13,239
Doesn't he look like a cat? See?

38
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,240
Jeez.

39
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,360
How sweet.

40
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,840
He's a cat.

41
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:19,240
An orange cat.

42
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,280
Hey, I saw your content too, Dean.

43
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:24,640
With that tall, tanned guy. Who is he?

44
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,640
Ah.

45
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,840
He's a friend from the same stage play.

46
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:34,000
I made some content to promote it.

47
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:34,640
Ah.

48
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:37,360
It's grabbing attention.
People are really into it.

49
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,280
They're even shipping you two together.

50
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:42,880
Mm.

51
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,080
That's not happening.

52
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,040
My real man is right here.

53
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,720
Whoa, what?

54
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:50,640
What's this, dude?

55
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,520
I didn't know you two got back together.

56
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:54,920
Well…

57
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,360
It's recent.

58
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,599
It's good, though.

59
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:03,600
You know, he was miserable
for a month after the breakup, Dean.

60
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,000
It's true.

61
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:07,360
He kept calling, trying
to get me to go out.

62
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,679
But I refused. I wasn't that guy anymore.

63
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,280
I've been good since I got with Mew.

64
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,959
Oh, please.

65
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,040
I'm a different person now.

66
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,960
Oh, Jack, we'll come watch your play.

67
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,600
Ever since you switched faculties,
you look much happier.

68
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:22,640
Come.

69
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:26,160
I wrote the script, I'm directing,
and my boyfriend's the lead.

70
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,680
We need to step up our game.

71
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,080
Mm.

72
00:03:29,081 --> 00:03:30,321
We can't let them out-sweet us.

73
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:34,640
We should get going. We've got a shoot.

74
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,680
Alright. See you.

75
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:36,520
Bye, man.

76
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:38,000
Bye—oh, wait.

77
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,600
Read my messages.

78
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,760
I want you to direct a video for my client.

79
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:49,336
And you still haven't replied in the
high school group chat about the reunion.

80
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,320
I'm waiting on your answer.

81
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,640
Right. I'll reply.

82
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,319
I'll be waiting.

83
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,359
Yeah. See you.

84
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,360
See you.

85
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,480
Later.

86
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,280
- See you, Dean.
- See you.

87
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:09,680
Who knew true love
could rewrite Top like that?

88
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:36,000
"Only Friends : Dream On"

89
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,800
The night of the outing…

90
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,560
Let me be honest.

91
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,480
I was drunk.

92
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:03,920
I wasn't thinking about what I was doing.

93
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:13,080
But I really do see you as a friend.

94
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:21,440
I think you know Jack's the
one I want more than anything.

95
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,800
And more importantly,

96
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:31,360
Tua is my dearest friend
and I care about him deeply.

97
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:36,560
If he finds out about this,
he'll be so damn heartbroken.

98
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,600
Then let me be honest too.

99
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,920
Mm.

100
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:53,040
At first, I wasn't sure if what I
felt came from the play or real life.

101
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:59,320
But that night made it clear.
I don't have real feelings for you.

102
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:03,280
Because there's already
someone I have feelings for.

103
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:14,760
Mhm.

104
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,960
Good. We're on the same page.

105
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:21,240
That way, we can keep working together
without it getting awkward.

106
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,720
And I'm really sorry for
putting you in a difficult position.

107
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,200
Don't apologize.

108
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:31,320
Honestly, we were both in the wrong.

109
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:34,680
We're good?

110
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:35,960
Mm.

111
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,640
We're good.

112
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,400
You don't have to follow me.

113
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:10,160
Did you hear what I said back there?

114
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,320
Not much.

115
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:21,440
Dean.

116
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:24,000
Don't think no one
notices what you're doing.

117
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,640
You should be more careful.

118
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,360
What are you talking about?

119
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,160
Not everyone's on your side.

120
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,440
Someone wants to see you fall.

121
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,000
I know.

122
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,960
The only one who hates me is Raffy.

123
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:47,120
Don't tell me
Raffy knows about Arnold and me.

124
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Shit.

125
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:58,720
Let's just say we were somewhere
we weren't supposed to be.

126
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,120
This time, you're out of luck.

127
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,600
Raffy recorded a video of you and Arnold.

128
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:16,080
Even if you say nothing happened,
one video can spark a hundred rumors.

129
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,560
Damn it!

130
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:25,960
Can you help me?

131
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,480
Dean.

132
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,680
I don't know how I can help you this time.

133
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,600
You should talk to Raffy yourself.

134
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:33,640
Like he'd ever help me.

135
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,400
You know he wants
Jack and me to break up.

136
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,240
Rome.

137
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:51,840
If you help me this time,
you'll be saving everyone.

138
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,000
If that video gets out…

139
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,200
the faculty play is over.

140
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:17,080
A new painting technique?
You paint on your face now?

141
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,920
I was just thinking about things.

142
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,160
How old are you again?

143
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,520
Do I still have to take care of you? Huh?

144
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:28,400
Wow, you two made up,
and suddenly work's moving fast.

145
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,480
Why? You jealous?

146
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,360
If you are, go find someone.

147
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:36,240
It's not like I'm not looking.
I just haven't found the right one.

148
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,960
Focus and finish the painting.

149
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,480
How's it going over here?

150
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,200
Here, have some water.

151
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,080
Thanks.

152
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:51,880
Should we plan a trip
or do something together?

153
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:54,833
What's gotten into you?

154
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:57,760
Opening night's in two weeks.

155
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,760
I don't want you stressing out.

156
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,160
Don't you want to go?

157
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:03,760
I do.

158
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,440
I'll go anywhere with you.

159
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:06,800
Who else is coming?

160
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,720
Just the two of us is enough.

161
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,800
Come outside with me.
I need to talk to you about something.

162
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,000
What is it?

163
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,560
I said, let's talk outside.

164
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:43,840
Raffy, don't leak
that video of Dean and Arnold.

165
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,480
I think you should just delete it.

166
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:51,640
Why should I listen to you?

167
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,200
Just trust me.

168
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:54,880
You can't let this get out.

169
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:56,360
And why not?

170
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,360
Are you really just
going to let those two off the hook?

171
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:05,360
Remember when you
exposed Dean as a host?

172
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,160
Did it even affect him?

173
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:13,440
And if you expose him again this time,
you'll be the one who looks bad.

174
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,759
So you're worried about me or about Dean?

175
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:17,760
Hey, can't you just listen to me for once?
Screw this!

176
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,560
Who you care about is your business.

177
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:25,880
And whether I leak that
video or not, that's mine.

178
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,520
Gosh.

179
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,560
I didn't know you were into
this kind of dancing.

180
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,920
When did you take
an interest in swing dance?

181
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,800
I saw their annual event video.

182
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:57,359
They dressed up so nicely,
I wanted to dress up too.

183
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,640
And I wanted to dance with you.

184
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,360
So here we are.

185
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:02,040
Okay.

186
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:06,000
Hi, guys. Let's start with
the basics of swing dance.

187
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:10,880
But before we begin, decide with your
partner who's leading and who's following.

188
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,560
Talk it out.

189
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,840
You lead. I'll follow.

190
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:16,560
Sure.

191
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:21,279
Now that we've got roles,
leaders, offer your hands.

192
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,880
Followers, take them.

193
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,200
Relax your arms.

194
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:28,120
And while you're dancing,
look into each other's eyes.

195
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,520
Hey, look at me.

196
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,080
Don't be shy.

197
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,880
Well, you're staring at me.

198
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,280
Anyone would get shy.

199
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,840
If you're ready, let's go.

200
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:49,399
Six, five… six, let's go.

201
00:13:49,400 --> 00:14:00,600
One, two, three. Aha!

202
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:35,880
Who knew this would be
harder than your TikTok dances?

203
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:40,560
It's fine. Think of it as
trying something new together.

204
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:44,320
Besides, I like it when you dance.

205
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,240
It's cute.

206
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,280
Okay. Now I'm motivated to keep going.

207
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,520
Just dance, Tua.

208
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,440
Don't forget, you've got your own
personal instructor right here.

209
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,200
Okay?

210
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:21,600
Dancing with Tua was fun.

211
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:26,040
His rhythm is unlike
anyone else's I've known.

212
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:51,040
You can't just drag me around everywhere.

213
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:56,440
No matter how nice you are to me,
I'm not deleting that video.

214
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:00,040
I'm done getting involved in your drama.

215
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,240
I just wanted to bring you here.

216
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:07,600
They hired me as a DJ,
so I wanted to check out the vibe first.

217
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:12,240
Drinking in the daytime?

218
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:14,920
Mm.

219
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:18,280
Day party. People are into it these days.

220
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,920
You don't have to drink alcohol.
Non-alcoholic drinks can be fun too.

221
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,000
Such a Gen Z thing.

222
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,080
Cool, right?

223
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:09,160
Hey, finished your drink?

224
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:10,840
Mm.

225
00:17:11,096 --> 00:17:12,375
You want me to get it?

226
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,440
It's fine, I'll get it.

227
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,040
Excuse me.

228
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:18,720
Excuse me.

229
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:21,800
Excuse me.

230
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,800
Two, please.

231
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:34,199
Hey. Make it quick.

232
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,200
Yeah.

233
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,720
Rome.

234
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:07,760
It's done.

235
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:09,840
Thank you, man.

236
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,400
What are you looking for?

237
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,520
I lost my phone.
What?

238
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:28,120
How?

239
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,880
I didn't even take it out.

240
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:33,240
Maybe someone took it?

241
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,000
Who would do that?

242
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,840
Let me help you look.

243
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,160
May I please put these here for now?

244
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,600
Hey.

245
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,600
Here.

246
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:05,080
I found it right there.

247
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,080
Having too much fun, huh?

248
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:08,880
You didn't even notice you dropped it.

249
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,200
Good thing no one stepped on it.

250
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,240
Here.

251
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:15,240
Holy shit.

252
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,720
I thought it was gone.

253
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:22,000
Come on, let's get back to the fun.

254
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,520
He won't listen to me.

255
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:35,040
I had to do it this way.

256
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,440
Gosh.

257
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:58,320
Look. Fencing's fun,
but it's kind of exhausting.

258
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:03,560
It's fun when your opponent matches you.

259
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,000
Like you and me.

260
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,440
Wow, aren't you sweet?

261
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:13,800
Hey.
Hm?

262
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:17,400
How are things with your sister Dao?

263
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,080
Same as always.

264
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:23,680
Back with her boyfriend
for the hundredth time.

265
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:30,280
Little bro here barked for nothing.

266
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:32,960
Come on.

267
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:35,040
At least she's okay.

268
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,440
Mm.

269
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,200
What about you?

270
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:39,760
Hm?

271
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,520
Have you talked to your mom?

272
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:48,360
Ever since I moved out, not really.

273
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:54,280
Besides, she has a new family now.

274
00:20:57,320 --> 00:21:00,800
I think she misses you too.

275
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:06,400
Why not give her a chance? Hm?

276
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,520
Okay.

277
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,000
I won't push.

278
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,120
Do whatever you're comfortable with.

279
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,200
It's not that.

280
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,920
I just realized
there's somewhere I want to go.

281
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:34,360
After the exam tomorrow,
want to come with me?

282
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:47,800
Wherever you go, I'm coming with you.

283
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,400
Remember your own words.

284
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,040
Mm.

285
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:54,840
For now…

286
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,440
let's keep practicing.

287
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,600
Oh, come on, Jack.

288
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:00,679
- Let's go.
- Jack.

289
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:03,000
This time, I'm beating your ass.

290
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:04,720
Get up.

291
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:06,000
Wait.

292
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,080
What?

293
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,720
Give me a kiss on the cheek first.

294
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,480
Come on, I need the energy.

295
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,200
Do it.

296
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:17,720
One more.

297
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,040
No. That's enough.

298
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:20,800
Come on. Get up.

299
00:22:20,801 --> 00:22:21,840
Jeez.

300
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,720
I'm ready to start over.

301
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:28,760
Rome really just saved my life.

302
00:22:35,860 --> 00:22:38,140
Aren't you afraid,
coming to see me like this?

303
00:22:39,780 --> 00:22:41,756
If we love each other,
what's there to be afraid of?

304
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:43,380
Project your voice, Raffy.

305
00:22:52,540 --> 00:22:54,340
Aren't you afraid,
coming to see me like this?

306
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:57,500
If we love each other,
what's there to be afraid of?

307
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:04,500
Cut!

308
00:23:11,340 --> 00:23:13,300
I think we're done for today.

309
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:16,540
Sorry. Can we go again?

310
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:18,420
I couldn't focus properly just now.

311
00:23:19,620 --> 00:23:20,620
Raffy…

312
00:23:22,060 --> 00:23:23,380
That was so tense.

313
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:26,820
Your eyes didn't say you want each other.

314
00:23:30,660 --> 00:23:33,020
That's a wrap for today. You're dismissed.

315
00:23:36,095 --> 00:23:38,140
Jack, please. One more round.

316
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:42,980
It's fine. Don't force it.

317
00:23:43,580 --> 00:23:45,940
The more you push,
the more stressed out you'll be.

318
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:48,020
Just take a break.

319
00:24:26,140 --> 00:24:29,419
You fought so hard for the lead…

320
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:31,100
and this is all you've got?

321
00:24:35,260 --> 00:24:37,020
No one to blame but yourself.

322
00:24:37,820 --> 00:24:39,580
You just suck so bad.

323
00:24:49,220 --> 00:24:51,820
You're right. Who'd be like you?

324
00:24:52,060 --> 00:24:55,300
So dedicated you had to sneak off for a
little one-on-one rehearsal at the outing.

325
00:24:55,940 --> 00:25:00,260
Does Jack know being a host isn't just
your job, it's who you are at your core?

326
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:05,219
What are you talking about? Hm?

327
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:06,340
The truth.

328
00:25:07,140 --> 00:25:08,540
The truth, with proof.

329
00:25:09,460 --> 00:25:14,380
I'd love to know how Jack sees you
when he finds out.

330
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:18,460
Where's your proof?

331
00:25:37,820 --> 00:25:39,460
Words are just words.

332
00:25:40,260 --> 00:25:44,180
Run your mouth all you want.
No one's buying it.

333
00:25:49,780 --> 00:25:51,100
What did you do to my phone?

334
00:25:51,460 --> 00:25:53,100
How could I do anything to your phone?

335
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:55,300
It's been with you the whole time.

336
00:26:03,340 --> 00:26:04,420
Dean, you bastard.

337
00:26:06,060 --> 00:26:09,700
If you're coming for me,
you better watch your back.

338
00:26:19,660 --> 00:26:20,660
Damn it.

339
00:26:21,820 --> 00:26:25,140
He's nowhere near me…
in terms of skill or brains.

340
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:38,140
Hey.

341
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:39,420
You done rehearsing?

342
00:26:40,020 --> 00:26:42,820
Mm. Jack really tore into us today.

343
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:46,300
That's just how he is.

344
00:26:46,420 --> 00:26:48,860
The closer we get to opening night,
the more wound up he gets.

345
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,900
Don't overthink it.

346
00:26:51,204 --> 00:26:52,451
Just do your best!

347
00:26:55,980 --> 00:26:57,700
Let me take your measurements.

348
00:26:58,340 --> 00:26:59,340
Jacket off.

349
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:11,260
And try to stay in shape during this time.

350
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:15,660
If I finish your costume and it
doesn't fit, I'm coming for you.

351
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:17,900
Oh, wow, Tua.

352
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:19,500
Yes, sir.

353
00:27:20,420 --> 00:27:22,180
So, how's rehearsing with Raffy?

354
00:27:22,780 --> 00:27:24,100
Different from working with Dean?

355
00:27:24,300 --> 00:27:25,540
With Raffy…

356
00:27:25,860 --> 00:27:26,900
Yeah, it's different.

357
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:30,580
I'm trying to reach him emotionally,
but it's not landing.

358
00:27:31,220 --> 00:27:33,140
I feel more when I act with Dean.

359
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:37,580
But during the audition,

360
00:27:37,900 --> 00:27:41,860
when I had to improvise and hit on you,
that felt the most real.

361
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:54,300
Jacket back on.

362
00:27:54,460 --> 00:27:55,460
You're done?

363
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,220
Damn you, Jack.

364
00:28:13,580 --> 00:28:15,156
Why didn't you tell me
you were taking me to see your dad?

365
00:28:15,180 --> 00:28:17,260
What if I showed up looking a mess?

366
00:28:18,100 --> 00:28:20,620
My dad doesn't judge people
by their appearances.

367
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:24,500
So what's this?

368
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:28,740
You're bringing me to meet your dad…
as his son-in-law?

369
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:31,820
You always make it about you.

370
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:33,940
I just miss my dad.

371
00:28:38,220 --> 00:28:39,220
Take your time.

372
00:28:40,740 --> 00:28:41,780
- Hi, Dad.
- Hello, sir.

373
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:43,300
Hey, guys.

374
00:28:43,580 --> 00:28:44,220
Wait.

375
00:28:44,500 --> 00:28:46,060
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

376
00:28:46,420 --> 00:28:47,580
It's a surprise.

377
00:28:48,300 --> 00:28:50,340
How have you been?

378
00:28:51,260 --> 00:28:54,660
Quite busy. Lots of orders lately.

379
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:57,420
So what's this?

380
00:28:58,180 --> 00:28:59,300
Are you two back together?

381
00:29:02,860 --> 00:29:03,860
Yes, Dad.

382
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:07,940
Then let this love
take you somewhere better.

383
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:09,820
Don't lose it like last time.

384
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:15,300
I promise I won't
break your son's heart again, sir.

385
00:29:16,660 --> 00:29:18,020
You're my witness.

386
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:23,060
Hello?

387
00:29:23,820 --> 00:29:24,820
What?

388
00:29:24,940 --> 00:29:26,460
You alright? Is it bad?

389
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:30,100
Okay. Got it.

390
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:35,700
What happened?

391
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:39,860
My regular delivery
guy got into an accident.

392
00:29:40,180 --> 00:29:41,580
He's waiting on insurance.

393
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:45,700
He probably won't
make the deliveries on time.

394
00:29:49,300 --> 00:29:50,140
How about this?

395
00:29:50,141 --> 00:29:52,420
I'll handle the deliveries.
I've got time today.

396
00:29:52,940 --> 00:29:53,940
That's right, sir.

397
00:29:56,700 --> 00:29:57,700
Uh…

398
00:29:58,900 --> 00:29:59,900
Mm.

399
00:30:00,100 --> 00:30:01,260
Then I'll leave it to you.

400
00:30:01,980 --> 00:30:03,140
You'll have several stops.

401
00:30:03,620 --> 00:30:06,620
And at the last one,
don't forget the flowers.

402
00:30:06,820 --> 00:30:09,299
The customer wants it to be a surprise.

403
00:30:09,300 --> 00:30:11,140
He's proposing on their
seventh anniversary.

404
00:30:11,940 --> 00:30:13,340
Okay, Dad. No problem.

405
00:30:28,220 --> 00:30:29,220
The hell?!

406
00:30:34,740 --> 00:30:37,740
You took me out
to delete the video on my phone?

407
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:41,260
We'll talk later. Let me finish work first.

408
00:30:43,340 --> 00:30:45,060
Did you really have to go this far for him?

409
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:46,100
Did he pay you?

410
00:30:48,260 --> 00:30:49,940
He didn't.

411
00:30:50,140 --> 00:30:51,340
Don't get frustrated just yet.

412
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:52,340
Let's take this outside.

413
00:30:52,420 --> 00:30:53,420
No. We're talking now.

414
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:55,460
Explain it.

415
00:30:55,733 --> 00:30:59,173
Tell me you didn't take me out
just to delete Dean's video.

416
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:02,700
Answer me!

417
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:04,220
Damn it! What the hell is going on?

418
00:31:04,780 --> 00:31:07,100
If you're going to fight,
think about my customers.

419
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:08,300
Huh?

420
00:31:08,780 --> 00:31:09,780
Take it outside.

421
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:13,180
Sorry, sis.
Give me a minute.

422
00:31:27,420 --> 00:31:28,940
Why are you protecting Dean?

423
00:31:29,500 --> 00:31:30,780
I'm not protecting him.

424
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:32,660
I just don't want this to escalate.

425
00:31:32,900 --> 00:31:34,460
You saw it. They didn't do anything.

426
00:31:35,039 --> 00:31:36,279
A hug was nasty enough.

427
00:31:36,507 --> 00:31:38,707
But that's all it was.

428
00:31:39,427 --> 00:31:42,067
How would you know?
They were alone in the woods.

429
00:31:42,439 --> 00:31:44,119
You and I hooked up, didn't we?

430
00:31:45,273 --> 00:31:46,273
Or what?

431
00:31:46,553 --> 00:31:48,153
You don't like Jack, so you don't care?

432
00:31:48,367 --> 00:31:49,367
Hey.

433
00:31:50,540 --> 00:31:52,860
This has nothing to do
with whether I like Jack or not.

434
00:31:53,246 --> 00:31:54,582
Why are you dragging him into this anyway?

435
00:31:54,820 --> 00:31:55,899
He's none of your concern.

436
00:31:55,900 --> 00:31:57,100
He is! Because I like Jack.

437
00:31:58,900 --> 00:32:01,220
He shouldn't get his heart broken
by an asshole like Dean.

438
00:32:07,566 --> 00:32:09,246
So you're going to keep liking Jack?

439
00:32:09,873 --> 00:32:10,873
Right.

440
00:32:11,293 --> 00:32:12,813
It's fine that I don't have proof.

441
00:32:13,586 --> 00:32:14,866
But Jack needs to know.

442
00:32:15,700 --> 00:32:16,700
I'll tell him.

443
00:32:17,226 --> 00:32:18,346
Will you just stop already?!

444
00:32:21,206 --> 00:32:22,206
Have you had enough?

445
00:32:25,153 --> 00:32:26,713
Will you stop doing things for Jack?

446
00:32:27,473 --> 00:32:29,833
No matter what you do,
he won't see your worth.

447
00:32:31,100 --> 00:32:32,740
The one who likes you is right here.

448
00:32:32,919 --> 00:32:34,199
A loser is right here!

449
00:32:39,420 --> 00:32:41,780
I did everything for you.
I helped you in every way I could.

450
00:32:43,100 --> 00:32:44,180
Damn it.

451
00:32:44,379 --> 00:32:46,059
When will I ever be in your line of sight?

452
00:32:46,620 --> 00:32:47,940
When will you see my worth?

453
00:32:56,100 --> 00:32:57,100
Rome.

454
00:32:58,540 --> 00:33:01,900
Someone like you… is not for me.

455
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:33,960
Good evening.

456
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:36,293
Good evening. I'm here with a delivery.

457
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,720
The order is under Ms. Nilobol.

458
00:33:38,340 --> 00:33:39,340
I see.

459
00:33:39,380 --> 00:33:42,540
It's the lady in pink, sitting inside.

460
00:33:46,580 --> 00:33:46,860
Thank you.
Please.

461
00:33:47,780 --> 00:33:48,780
Thank you.

462
00:33:53,220 --> 00:33:55,780
Hey. She's alone.

463
00:33:56,140 --> 00:33:57,220
Perfect timing.

464
00:33:58,420 --> 00:33:59,500
I'll give this to her.

465
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:07,820
Happy seven-year anniversary.

466
00:34:08,220 --> 00:34:09,220
Yes?

467
00:34:12,060 --> 00:34:13,060
What is this?

468
00:34:13,220 --> 00:34:17,260
Your boyfriend asked me to tell you,
"Will you marry me?"

469
00:34:23,580 --> 00:34:24,580
Jack.

470
00:34:25,260 --> 00:34:27,020
Who's asking my wife to marry him?

471
00:34:27,740 --> 00:34:28,740
Who the hell are you?

472
00:34:29,140 --> 00:34:31,540
I'm just here to deliver the flowers.

473
00:34:35,700 --> 00:34:36,916
Are you my wife's secret lover?

474
00:34:36,940 --> 00:34:37,940
Or do you know him?

475
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:39,900
No, sir. I'm just the messenger.

476
00:34:40,140 --> 00:34:41,140
Messenger, my ass!

477
00:34:41,260 --> 00:34:43,140
You just said, "Will you marry me?"

478
00:34:43,860 --> 00:34:44,540
Calm down, sir.

479
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:46,619
Please, just listen. Take it easy.

480
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:47,859
I'm not listening to a damn thing.

481
00:34:47,860 --> 00:34:48,860
Will you just listen?

482
00:34:49,180 --> 00:34:50,500
You bastard! Did you just hit me?

483
00:34:50,780 --> 00:34:51,420
Jack!

484
00:34:51,660 --> 00:34:52,660
Honey, don't!

485
00:34:53,300 --> 00:34:54,460
Are you defending your lover?

486
00:34:55,780 --> 00:34:57,660
Jack, come on. Run!

487
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:43,900
That was close.

488
00:35:45,140 --> 00:35:47,140
We almost got stabbed to death
and failed as Cupid.

489
00:35:48,540 --> 00:35:50,220
Yeah, no kidding.

490
00:35:53,780 --> 00:35:56,820
Hey, do you realize now
you gave it to the wrong woman?

491
00:35:57,300 --> 00:36:00,100
What?! Why didn't you tell me?

492
00:36:00,820 --> 00:36:01,860
Did I have time?

493
00:36:03,220 --> 00:36:04,420
Damn.

494
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:10,700
That was no romance. It was totally action.

495
00:36:12,460 --> 00:36:15,100
We can still do romance.

496
00:36:15,980 --> 00:36:17,260
Action romance.

497
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:38,580
Happy three-year anniversary.

498
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:42,540
Will you marry me?

499
00:36:45,900 --> 00:36:48,500
You just wanted to
give your boyfriend a flower.

500
00:36:48,580 --> 00:36:50,076
Did you have to make it this dramatic?

501
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:53,100
So? Yes or no?

502
00:36:54,820 --> 00:36:56,900
Is this the time to joke around?

503
00:36:59,820 --> 00:37:04,700
I'm joking now, but if we're
still together in the future…

504
00:37:07,940 --> 00:37:09,100
I'd want to get married.

505
00:37:15,459 --> 00:37:16,539
I don't know.

506
00:37:18,359 --> 00:37:23,079
Let's wait until then.
You can ask me again.

507
00:37:25,173 --> 00:37:26,173
Okay.

508
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:30,820
Shit!

509
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:17,340
- Hey!
- I got it.

510
00:38:25,953 --> 00:38:26,993
That took forever.

511
00:38:47,820 --> 00:38:48,820
Hey.

512
00:38:48,980 --> 00:38:49,380
Hm?

513
00:38:49,780 --> 00:38:50,780
Let go.

514
00:38:53,700 --> 00:38:55,140
I'm not letting you go anymore, Tua.

515
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:57,220
I've let this go on for too long.

516
00:38:58,700 --> 00:38:59,900
What are you talking about?

517
00:39:03,260 --> 00:39:06,260
All this time, I knew
how you felt about me.

518
00:39:08,660 --> 00:39:09,740
I just pretended not to.

519
00:39:12,220 --> 00:39:14,380
Now I realize the problem was me.

520
00:39:14,820 --> 00:39:17,980
I was too scared
to go from friends to boyfriends.

521
00:39:20,180 --> 00:39:25,140
That's why I left you hanging, confused,
because I couldn't be clear.

522
00:39:28,460 --> 00:39:29,860
I didn't blame you, did I?

523
00:39:31,460 --> 00:39:35,860
Now it's clear to you
how we feel about each other.

524
00:39:40,140 --> 00:39:42,380
But I want to make it clearer.

525
00:39:53,753 --> 00:39:55,473
I like you as more than just a friend, Tua.

526
00:39:58,660 --> 00:40:01,900
And I'm not afraid anymore
to be your boyfriend.

527
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:13,380
Tua.

528
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:17,580
Will you be my boyfriend?

529
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:19,420
Huh?

530
00:40:19,740 --> 00:40:22,940
I asked, "Will you be my boyfriend?"

531
00:40:28,100 --> 00:40:29,100
Mm.

532
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:47,180
Wow, I'm actually blushing.

533
00:41:57,580 --> 00:41:58,580
(Next Episode)
What is it?

534
00:41:58,605 --> 00:41:59,605
Jack didn't want you?

535
00:41:59,699 --> 00:42:00,699
So you came to me?

536
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:06,220
Who would've thought I'd end up
dating the amusement park owner's son?

537
00:42:06,540 --> 00:42:08,340
Are you two dating?

538
00:42:08,460 --> 00:42:10,260
If I know, I'll know how to act.

539
00:42:12,980 --> 00:42:14,860
There's something
important I need to tell you.

540
00:42:17,220 --> 00:42:18,500
Jack, damn it, listen to me!

541
00:42:20,060 --> 00:42:22,076
You told me to trust you.
You said it was just content.

542
00:42:22,100 --> 00:42:22,700
What the hell was that?

543
00:42:23,020 --> 00:42:24,580
Please don't leave me.
